{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775888812518,"sessionID":"ses_284c75d2fffevadkVQj66gScq2","part":{"id":"prt_d7b38c77f001wYAfBW69dDLI2p","messageID":"msg_d7b38b8b10019eDZpJ9ih6FA8o","sessionID":"ses_284c75d2fffevadkVQj66gScq2","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-f79af56ffa6a47b6849e4d0dee6c1a08","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/integrations/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/integrations/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AgentCube Integrations — Design\n2: \n3: Sources: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/integrations/dify-plugin/`, `/tmp/agentcube-ref/example/pcap-analyzer/`.\n4: \n5: ## Dify plugin — file map\n6: \n7: | File | Role |\n8: |------|------|\n9: | `main.py` | `Plugin(DifyPluginEnv(MAX_REQUEST_TIMEOUT=120)).run()` |\n10: | `manifest.yaml` | Root plugin manifest for Dify |\n11: | `provider/agentcube.yaml` | Tool provider identity + tool list + Python entry |\n12: | `provider/agentcube.py` | `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterProvider` |\n13: | `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml` | Tool parameter schema |\n14: | `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.py` | `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool` |\n15: | `requirements.txt` | `dify-plugin` + `agentcube-sdk` pins |\n16: | `GUIDE.md`, `README.md`, `PRIVACY.md`, `.difyignore` | Docs / packaging |\n17: \n18: ## `manifest.yaml` structure (exact top-level keys)\n19: \n20: From source:\n21: \n22: - `version`: `0.0.2`\n23: - `type`: `plugin`\n24: - `author`: `volcano-sh`\n25: - `name`: `agentcube`\n26: - `label`: map `en_US`, `ja_JP`, `zh_Hans`, `pt_BR` → `Agentcube`\n27: - `description`: multilingual strings (AgentCube description)\n28: - `icon`: `icon.png`\n29: - `icon_dark`: `icon-dark.png`\n30: - `resource`: `memory`, `permission` subtree (`tool`, `model`, `endpoint`, `app`, `storage` flags and sizes)\n31: - `plugins.tools`: list `[provider/agentcube.yaml]`\n32: - `meta`: `version`, `arch` (`amd64`, `arm64`), `runner` (`language: python`, `version: \"3.12\"`, `entrypoint: main`), `minimum_dify_version: null`\n33: - `created_at`, `privacy`, `repo`, `verified`\n34: \n35: ## `provider/agentcube.yaml` structure\n36: \n37: - `identity`: `author`, `name`, `label` (multilingual), `description` (multilingual), `icon`\n38: - Commented `oauth_schema` block (not active)\n39: - `tools`: list `[tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml]`\n40: - `extra.python.source`: `provider/agentcube.py`\n41: \n42: ## Tool definition (`tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml`)\n43: \n44: - `identity.name`: `agentcube-code-interpreter`\n45: - `identity.author`: `agentcube`\n46: - `identity.label` / `description` (human + llm strings)\n47: - `parameters` (each has `name`, `type`, `required`, `label`, `human_description`, `llm_description`, `form`):\n48: \n49: | name | type | required | form | notes |\n50: |------|------|----------|------|-------|\n51: | `router_url` | string | true | form | |\n52: | `workload_manager_url` | string | true | form | |\n53: | `language` | select | false | llm | options: `python`, `javascript`, `typescript` |\n54: | `code` | string | false | llm | |\n55: | `command` | string | false | llm | |\n56: | `session_id` | string | false | llm | |\n57: | `session_reuse` | boolean | false | llm | |\n58: | `code_interpreter_id` | string | false | llm | |\n59: \n60: - `extra.python.source`: `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.py`\n61: \n62: ## Provider implementation (`provider/agentcube.py`)\n63: \n64: ```python\n65: from dify_plugin import ToolProvider\n66: from dify_plugin.errors.tool import ToolProviderCredentialValidationError\n67: \n68: class AgentcubeCodeInterpreterProvider(ToolProvider):\n69:     def _validate_credentials(self, credentials: dict[str, Any]) -> None:\n70:         try:\n71:             \"\"\" IMPLEMENT YOUR VALIDATION HERE \"\"\"\n72:         except Exception as e:\n73:             raise ToolProviderCredentialValidationError(str(e))\n74: ```\n75: \n76: (OAuth helper methods are present only as comments.)\n77: \n78: ## Tool implementation (`tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.py`)\n79: \n80: ```python\n81: from collections.abc import Generator\n82: from typing import Any\n83: from dify_plugin import Tool\n84: from dify_plugin.entities.tool import ToolInvokeMessage\n85: from agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient\n86: \n87: class AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool(Tool):\n88:     def _invoke(self, tool_parameters: dict[str, Any]) -> Generator[ToolInvokeMessage]:\n89:         result = self.execute(**tool_parameters)\n90:         yield self.create_json_message(result)\n91: \n92:     def execute(\n93:         self,\n94:         router_url=None,\n95:         workload_manager_url=None,\n96:         language=\"python\",\n97:         code_interpreter_id=None,\n98:         session_id=None,\n99:         code=None,\n100:         command=None,\n101:         session_reuse=False,\n102:         **kwargs\n103:     ): ...\n104: ```\n105: \n106: ## Plugin dependencies (`integrations/dify-plugin/requirements.txt`)\n107: \n108: ```\n109: dify-plugin>=0.4.2,<0.5.0\n110: agentcube-sdk>=0.0.10\n111: ```\n112: \n113: ## PCAP analyzer — application structure (`example/pcap-analyzer/`)\n114: \n115: | File | Role |\n116: |------|------|\n117: | `pcap_analyzer.py` | FastAPI app, agents, sandbox runner, analysis orchestration, `uvicorn` entry |\n118: | `requirements.txt` | FastAPI, uvicorn, LangChain / LangGraph stack, multipart, etc. |\n119: | `Dockerfile` | `uv` base image, installs reqs, copies `sdk-python/agentcube` + `pcap_analyzer.py` |\n120: | `deployment.yaml` | K8s Deployment + env for OpenAI-compatible API and AgentCube URLs |\n121: | `README.md` | Documentation |\n122: \n123: ## FastAPI application (`pcap_analyzer.py`)\n124: \n125: ### Globals / config (selected)\n126: \n127: | Name | Source | Default / value |\n128: |------|--------|-----------------|\n129: | `API_KEY` | `OPENAI_API_KEY` | required at startup |\n130: | `API_BASE_URL` | `OPENAI_API_BASE` | `https://api.siliconflow.cn/v1` |\n131: | `MODEL_NAME` | `OPENAI_MODEL` | `Qwen/QwQ-32B` |\n132: | `CODEINTERPRETER_NAME` | env | `my-interpreter` |\n133: | `SANDBOX_NAMESPACE` | env | `default` |\n134: | `SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC` | env | `5` |\n135: | `SERVER_HOST` | constant | `0.0.0.0` |\n136: | `SERVER_PORT` | constant | `8000` |\n137: | `SERVER_RELOAD` | constant | `True` |\n138: \n139: ### Core classes / functions\n140: \n141: ```python\n142: class SandboxRunner:\n143:     def __init__(self, name: str = \"my-interpreter\", namespace: str = \"default\", warmup_sec: int = 5): ...\n144:     def upload_file(self, local_path: str, remote_path: str) -> bool: ...\n145:     def upload_bytes(self, data: bytes, remote_path: str) -> bool: ...\n146:     def run(self, command: str) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n147:     def stop(self): ...\n148: \n149: def build_react_agent(llm, system_prompt: str): ...\n150: def invoke_react_agent(agent, user_text: str) -> str: ...\n151: def build_planner_agent(llm): ...\n152: def build_reporter_agent(llm): ...\n153: \n154: def _plan_script(agent, pcap_local_path: str) -> str: ...\n155: def _repair_script(agent, prev_script: str, results: List[Dict[str, Any]]) -> str: ...\n156: def _execute_once_in_runner(runner: SandboxRunner, pcap_local_path: str, script: str) -> List[Dict[str, Any]]: ...\n157: def _analyze_with_retries(..., max_retries: int = 2) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n158: def _report(agent, results: List[Dict[str, Any]]) -> str: ...\n159: \n160: class AnalyzeResponse(BaseModel):\n161:     script: str\n162:     results: List[Dict[str, Any]]\n163:     report: str\n164: \n165: app = FastAPI(title=\"PCAP Analyzer — Env-Only Config\")\n166: ```\n167: \n168: ### FastAPI endpoints\n169: \n170: | Method | Path | Signature / behavior |\n171: |--------|------|----------------------|\n172: | (event) | startup | `on_startup()` → builds `ChatOpenAI`, `PLANNER`, `REPORTER`; fails if no API key |\n173: | `POST` | `/analyze` | `async def analyze_endpoint(pcap_file: UploadFile = File(None), pcap_path: str = Form(None))` → `response_model=AnalyzeResponse` |\n174: \n175: ### Imports of note\n176: \n177: ```python\n178: from fastapi import FastAPI, UploadFile, File, Form, HTTPException\n179: from pydantic import BaseModel\n180: import uvicorn\n181: from langchain_openai import ChatOpenAI\n182: from langgraph.prebuilt import create_react_agent\n183: from langchain_core.messages import HumanMessage, AIMessage\n184: from agentcube.code_interpreter import CodeInterpreterClient\n185: from agentcube.exceptions import CommandExecutionError\n186: ```\n187: \n188: ## Kubernetes deployment (`deployment.yaml`)\n189: \n190: - `Deployment` `pcap-analyzer` in `namespace: default`\n191: - Container `pcap-analyzer`, image `pcap-analyzer:latest`, `imagePullPolicy: IfNotPresent`\n192: - Container port `8000` TCP\n193: - Resources: requests `cpu: 200m`, `memory: 100Mi`; limits `cpu: 1`, `memory: 1Gi`\n194: - Env: `OPENAI_API_KEY` from secret `pcap-analyzer-secrets` key `openai-api-key`; `OPENAI_API_BASE`, `OPENAI_MODEL`, `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`, `ROUTER_URL`, `CODEINTERPRETER_NAME`, `SANDBOX_NAMESPACE`, `SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC`\n195: - Command: `[\"uv\"]`, args: `[\"run\", \"pcap_analyzer.py\"]`\n196: \n197: ## Dockerfile highlights\n198: \n199: - Base: `ghcr.io/astral-sh/uv:python3.12-bookworm-slim`\n200: - `uv venv` + `uv pip install -r requirements.txt`\n201: - Copies `sdk-python/agentcube` → `./agentcube/`, `pcap_analyzer.py` → `./`\n202: - `ENV PYTHONPATH=\"/app\"`, exposes `8000`\n203: - `CMD [\"uv\", \"run\", \"pcap_analyzer.py\"]`\n204: \n205: ## PCAP example Python dependencies (`example/pcap-analyzer/requirements.txt`)\n206: \n207: Pinned packages include: `fastapi==0.120.0`, `uvicorn==0.38.0`, `langchain==1.0.2`, `langchain-classic==1.0.0`, `langchain-community==0.4.1`, `langchain-core==1.0.1`, `langchain-openai==1.0.1`, `langchain-text-splitters==1.0.0`, `langgraph==1.0.1`, `langgraph-checkpoint==3.0.0`, `langgraph-prebuilt==1.0.1`, `langgraph-sdk==0.2.9`, `langsmith==0.4.38`, `paramiko==4.0.0`, `python-multipart==0.0.20`\n208: \n209: *(The Dockerfile vendors `agentcube` from the monorepo copy; it is not listed in this `requirements.txt`.)*\n\n(End of file - total 209 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AgentCube Integrations — Design\n\nSources: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/integrations/dify-plugin/`, `/tmp/agentcube-ref/example/pcap-analyzer/`.\n\n## Dify plugin — file map\n\n| File | Role |\n|------|------|\n| `main.py` | `Plugin(DifyPluginEnv(MAX_REQUEST_TIMEOUT=120)).run()` |\n| `manifest.yaml` | Root plugin manifest for Dify |\n| `provider/agentcube.yaml` | Tool provider identity + tool list + Python entry |\n| `provider/agentcube.py` | `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterProvider` |\n| `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml` | Tool parameter schema |\n| `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.py` | `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool` |\n| `requirements.txt` | `dify-plugin` + `agentcube-sdk` pins |\n| `GUIDE.md`, `README.md`, `PRIVACY.md`, `.difyignore` | Docs / packaging |\n\n## `manifest.yaml` structure (exact top-level keys)\n\nFrom source:","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/integrations/design.md","time":{"start":1775888812498,"end":1775888812517}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775888812521,"sessionID":"ses_284c75d2fffevadkVQj66gScq2","part":{"id":"prt_d7b38c9b0001IF6x6r35Va14q5","messageID":"msg_d7b38b8b10019eDZpJ9ih6FA8o","sessionID":"ses_284c75d2fffevadkVQj66gScq2","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-174b90ba388d4254a2b8a61fa8654dcb","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/integrations/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/integrations/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Integrations Specification\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: Normative requirements for the AgentCube Dify plugin integration and the PCAP analyzer example that uses AgentCube code interpreters and Kubernetes sandboxes.\n6: \n7: ## Requirements\n8: \n9: ### Requirement: Dify plugin bootstrap and runtime\n10: \n11: The system SHALL expose a Dify-compatible Python plugin whose process entry runs the framework runner with a configured maximum request timeout.\n12: \n13: #### Scenario: Plugin process starts\n14: \n15: - **GIVEN** the plugin package is installed with compatible `dify-plugin` and `agentcube-sdk` versions\n16: - **WHEN** the platform starts the plugin using the manifest-declared entrypoint\n17: - **THEN** the plugin SHALL execute `main` which runs `Plugin(DifyPluginEnv(MAX_REQUEST_TIMEOUT=120)).run()` until the host stops it\n18: \n19: ---\n20: \n21: ### Requirement: Plugin manifest structure\n22: \n23: The system SHALL ship a root `manifest.yaml` declaring plugin metadata, tool provider registration, resource permissions, and runner metadata sufficient for Dify to load and execute the plugin.\n24: \n25: #### Scenario: Required manifest fields\n26: \n27: - **GIVEN** a valid plugin package root\n28: - **WHEN** the manifest is parsed by a Dify-compatible toolchain\n29: - **THEN** the manifest SHALL include `version`, `type: plugin`, `author`, `name`, `label` (multilingual map), `description` (multilingual), `icon`, `icon_dark`, `resource` (including `memory` and `permission` subtree), `plugins.tools` listing provider descriptors, and `meta` containing `version`, `arch`, `runner` (`language`, `version`, `entrypoint`), and `minimum_dify_version`\n30: \n31: #### Scenario: Tool provider wiring\n32: \n33: - **GIVEN** the manifest `plugins.tools` references the Agentcube provider descriptor\n34: - **WHEN** the plugin is loaded\n35: - **THEN** Dify SHALL resolve `provider/agentcube.yaml` and associate it with the Python module declared under `extra.python.source`\n36: \n37: ---\n38: \n39: ### Requirement: Provider descriptor structure\n40: \n41: The system SHALL define a tool provider YAML that identifies the provider, lists its tools, and points to the Python provider implementation.\n42: \n43: #### Scenario: Provider lists tools and entry module\n44: \n45: - **GIVEN** `provider/agentcube.yaml` is present\n46: - **WHEN** the integration runtime resolves the provider\n47: - **THEN** the descriptor SHALL include `identity` (author, name, multilingual label/description, icon), a `tools` list including `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml`, and `extra.python.source: provider/agentcube.py`\n48: \n49: ---\n50: \n51: ### Requirement: Tool parameter schema\n52: \n53: The system SHALL declare a tool schema for the code interpreter integration including connection endpoints, optional language selection, and code/command/session fields.\n54: \n55: #### Scenario: Declared parameters match remote APIs\n56: \n57: - **GIVEN** `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml`\n58: - **WHEN** an operator configures the tool in Dify\n59: - **THEN** the schema SHALL require string parameters `router_url` and `workload_manager_url`, SHALL offer optional `language` as a select among `python`, `javascript`, and `typescript`, and SHALL allow optional `code`, `command`, `session_id`, `session_reuse` (boolean), and `code_interpreter_id`, each documented for human and LLM-oriented forms\n60: \n61: ---\n62: \n63: ### Requirement: Tool provider credential validation\n64: \n65: The system SHALL implement credential validation on the tool provider class and SHALL surface validation failures using the Dify tool provider error type.\n66: \n67: #### Scenario: Invalid credentials are rejected\n68: \n69: - **GIVEN** an instance of `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterProvider`\n70: - **WHEN** `_validate_credentials` encounters an error condition the implementer treats as invalid\n71: - **THEN** the provider SHALL raise `ToolProviderCredentialValidationError` with a string message derived from the failure\n72: \n73: #### Scenario: Successful validation completes quietly\n74: \n75: - **GIVEN** credentials that satisfy the provider’s validation rules\n76: - **WHEN** `_validate_credentials` runs\n77: - **THEN** the method SHALL return without raising\n78: \n79: ---\n80: \n81: ### Requirement: Tool invocation and JSON messaging\n82: \n83: The system SHALL implement the Agentcube code interpreter tool as a Dify `Tool` that delegates execution and returns structured JSON to the host.\n84: \n85: #### Scenario: Dify invokes the tool\n86: \n87: - **GIVEN** a configured tool invocation with parameters matching the schema\n88: - **WHEN** Dify calls `_invoke` on `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool`\n89: - **THEN** the tool SHALL call `execute(**tool_parameters)` and SHALL yield `create_json_message(result)` for the outcome\n90: \n91: ---\n92: \n93: ### Requirement: Tool execution API surface\n94: \n95: The system SHALL implement `execute` with parameters for router and workload manager URLs, optional language, session controls, and code or command execution, delegating to `agentcube.CodeInterpreterClient`.\n96: \n97: #### Scenario: Code or command runs against configured endpoints\n98: \n99: - **GIVEN** valid `router_url`, `workload_manager_url`, and optional `language` defaulting to `python`\n100: - **WHEN** the tool receives `code` and/or `command` with optional `session_id`, `session_reuse`, and `code_interpreter_id`\n101: - **THEN** the tool SHALL use the AgentCube Python SDK client to perform the corresponding remote operations and SHALL return a JSON-serializable result object suitable for `create_json_message`\n102: \n103: ---\n104: \n105: ### Requirement: Plugin Python dependencies\n106: \n107: The system SHALL pin compatible versions of `dify-plugin` and `agentcube-sdk` for reproducible installs.\n108: \n109: #### Scenario: Dependency bounds\n110: \n111: - **GIVEN** `integrations/dify-plugin/requirements.txt`\n112: - **WHEN** dependencies are installed in a clean environment\n113: - **THEN** installs SHALL satisfy `dify-plugin>=0.4.2,<0.5.0` and `agentcube-sdk>=0.0.10`\n114: \n115: ---\n116: \n117: ### Requirement: PCAP analyzer FastAPI service\n118: \n119: The system SHALL provide a FastAPI application that validates OpenAI-compatible configuration at startup, composes LangChain/LangGraph agents, and exposes an analysis endpoint for PCAP uploads.\n120: \n121: #### Scenario: Startup requires API key\n122: \n123: - **GIVEN** the process is started without a usable `OPENAI_API_KEY` (or equivalent configured API key)\n124: - **WHEN** the application completes startup hooks\n125: - **THEN** startup SHALL fail rather than serve requests without credentials\n126: \n127: #### Scenario: Analyze endpoint accepts PCAP input\n128: \n129: - **GIVEN** a running service with valid LLM configuration\n130: - **WHEN** a client calls `POST /analyze` with either an uploaded PCAP file or a `pcap_path` form field\n131: - **THEN** the handler SHALL return a body matching `AnalyzeResponse` including `script`, `results`, and `report`\n132: \n133: ---\n134: \n135: ### Requirement: PCAP analyzer configuration surface\n136: \n137: The system SHALL read runtime configuration from environment variables for the OpenAI-compatible API, model selection, and AgentCube sandbox parameters.\n138: \n139: #### Scenario: Defaults and overrides\n140: \n141: - **GIVEN** standard deployment environment variables\n142: - **WHEN** the service starts\n143: - **THEN** it SHALL use `OPENAI_API_BASE` defaulting to `https://api.siliconflow.cn/v1`, `OPENAI_MODEL` defaulting to `Qwen/QwQ-32B`, `CODEINTERPRETER_NAME` defaulting to `my-interpreter`, `SANDBOX_NAMESPACE` defaulting to `default`, and `SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC` defaulting to `5`, while binding HTTP to `0.0.0.0:8000` as defined in the application\n144: \n145: ---\n146: \n147: ### Requirement: PCAP analyzer sandbox integration\n148: \n149: The system SHALL orchestrate PCAP analysis by planning and repairing scripts, executing them inside an AgentCube-backed sandbox via `SandboxRunner`, and aggregating results through reporter agents.\n150: \n151: #### Scenario: Sandbox runner executes commands\n152: \n153: - **GIVEN** a `SandboxRunner` constructed with interpreter name, namespace, and warmup duration\n154: - **WHEN** analysis logic invokes `run` with a shell command\n155: - **THEN** the runner SHALL execute the command in the remote sandbox context and SHALL return structured execution results for downstream LLM steps\n156: \n157: #### Scenario: File staging uses runner uploads\n158: \n159: - **GIVEN** a local PCAP path or bytes to analyze\n160: - **WHEN** the orchestration needs the artifact inside the sandbox workspace\n161: - **THEN** the system SHALL use `upload_file` or `upload_bytes` on `SandboxRunner` before executing analysis commands\n162: \n163: ---\n164: \n165: ### Requirement: PCAP analyzer container image\n166: \n167: The system SHALL build a container image that installs Python dependencies with `uv`, vendors the in-repo `agentcube` SDK copy, sets `PYTHONPATH`, exposes port 8000, and starts the FastAPI app via `uv run`.\n168: \n169: #### Scenario: Image entrypoint\n170: \n171: - **GIVEN** the `example/pcap-analyzer/Dockerfile` build context\n172: - **WHEN** the container runs without overriding the command\n173: - **THEN** the default command SHALL be `uv run pcap_analyzer.py` with `PYTHONPATH=\"/app\"` and port `8000` exposed\n174: \n175: ---\n176: \n177: ### Requirement: PCAP analyzer Kubernetes deployment\n178: \n179: The system SHALL supply a `Deployment` manifest that runs the analyzer image with resource requests/limits and environment variables wired from a Secret and plain env for AgentCube and model endpoints.\n180: \n181: #### Scenario: Deployment wiring\n182: \n183: - **GIVEN** `example/pcap-analyzer/deployment.yaml` applied to the cluster\n184: - **WHEN** the workload becomes ready\n185: - **THEN** the pod SHALL run image `pcap-analyzer:latest` (pull `IfNotPresent`), listen on TCP 8000, request `cpu: 200m` / `memory: 100Mi` and limit `cpu: 1` / `memory: 1Gi`, mount `OPENAI_API_KEY` from Secret `pcap-analyzer-secrets` key `openai-api-key`, and set `OPENAI_API_BASE`, `OPENAI_MODEL`, `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`, `ROUTER_URL`, `CODEINTERPRETER_NAME`, `SANDBOX_NAMESPACE`, and `SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC` as container environment variables\n186: \n187: #### Scenario: Process launch in cluster\n188: \n189: - **GIVEN** the deployment’s container specification\n190: - **WHEN** Kubernetes starts the container\n191: - **THEN** the command SHALL be `uv` with arguments `run pcap_analyzer.py`, matching local Docker behavior\n\n(End of file - total 191 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Integrations Specification\n\n## Purpose\n\nNormative requirements for the AgentCube Dify plugin integration and the PCAP analyzer example that uses AgentCube code interpreters and Kubernetes sandboxes.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Dify plugin bootstrap and runtime\n\nThe system SHALL expose a Dify-compatible Python plugin whose process entry runs the framework runner with a configured maximum request timeout.\n\n#### Scenario: Plugin process starts\n\n- **GIVEN** the plugin package is installed with compatible `dify-plugin` and `agentcube-sdk` versions\n- **WHEN** the platform starts the plugin using the manifest-declared entrypoint\n- **THEN** the plugin SHALL execute `main` which runs `Plugin(DifyPluginEnv(MAX_REQUEST_TIMEOUT=120)).run()` until the host stops it\n\n---\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/integrations/spec.md","time":{"start":1775888812499,"end":1775888812519}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775888812524,"sessionID":"ses_284c75d2fffevadkVQj66gScq2","part":{"id":"prt_d7b38c556001Hqq7lGEhb0Ykjw","messageID":"msg_d7b38b8b10019eDZpJ9ih6FA8o","sessionID":"ses_284c75d2fffevadkVQj66gScq2","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-89369309caf84b69bc223424a904257c","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-036/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-036/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-036 — Dify 插件集成 Tasks\n2: \n3: **Module**: `integrations`\n4: **Language**: Python\n5: **Size**: M\n6: \n7: ## Task Breakdown\n8: \n9: ### Task 1: Dify API client implementation\n10: - [ ] Review Dify API documentation\n11: - [ ] Design Dify client interface\n12: - [ ] Implement Dify API client class\n13: - [ ] Add authentication support\n14: - [ ] Add error handling\n15: - [ ] Add request/response logging\n16: \n17: **Verification**: Dify client can successfully authenticate and make API calls\n18: \n19: ---\n20: \n21: ### Task 2: Plugin registration mechanism\n22: - [ ] Design plugin registration interface\n23: - [ ] Implement plugin discovery\n24: - [ ] Implement plugin lifecycle management\n25: - [ ] Add plugin configuration validation\n26: - [ ] Add plugin health checks\n27: \n28: **Verification**: Plugins can be registered, discovered, and managed properly\n29: \n30: ---\n31: \n32: ### Task 3: Configuration management\n33: - [ ] Define Dify configuration schema\n34: - [ ] Implement configuration loading\n35: - [ ] Add environment variable support\n36: - [ ] Add configuration validation\n37: - [ ] Add configuration hot-reload support\n38: \n39: **Verification**: Configuration can be loaded and validated correctly\n40: \n41: ---\n42: \n43: ### Task 4: Error handling and retry logic\n44: - [ ] Implement error classification\n45: - [ ] Add retry mechanism for transient errors\n46: - [ ] Add circuit breaker pattern\n47: - [ ] Add timeout handling\n48: - [ ] Add error logging and metrics\n49: \n50: **Verification**: Errors are handled gracefully with appropriate retry logic\n51: \n52: ---\n53: \n54: ### Task 5: Unit tests\n55: - [ ] Write Dify client unit tests\n56: - [ ] Write plugin registration tests\n57: - [ ] Write configuration management tests\n58: - [ ] Write error handling tests\n59: - [ ] Achieve 80%+ code coverage\n60: \n61: **Verification**: All unit tests pass with high coverage\n62: \n63: ---\n64: \n65: ### Task 6: Integration tests\n66: - [ ] Write Dify API integration tests\n67: - [ ] Write end-to-end plugin tests\n68: - [ ] Test error scenarios\n69: - [ ] Test configuration scenarios\n70: \n71: **Verification**: All integration tests pass\n72: \n73: ---\n74: \n75: ### Task 7: Documentation\n76: - [ ] Write Dify integration documentation\n77: - [ ] Write plugin development guide\n78: - [ ] Write configuration reference\n79: - [ ] Add code examples\n80: \n81: **Verification**: Documentation is complete and accurate\n82: \n83: ---\n84: \n85: ## Summary\n86: \n87: **Total Tasks**: 7\n88: **Estimated Effort**: M (Medium) - 15-20 hours\n89: \n90: ### Key Deliverables\n91: 1. **Dify API client** with authentication and error handling\n92: 2. **Plugin registration mechanism** for Dify integration\n93: 3. **Configuration management** for Dify settings\n94: 4. **Comprehensive tests** (unit and integration)\n95: 5. **Complete documentation** for users and developers\n96: \n97: ### Success Criteria\n98: - Dify client can authenticate and make API calls successfully\n99: - Plugins can be registered and discovered properly\n100: - Configuration can be loaded and validated correctly\n101: - Error handling works with appropriate retry logic\n102: - All tests pass with 80%+ coverage\n103: - Documentation is complete and accurate\n104: \n105: ### Dependencies\n106: - Python 3.10+\n107: - Dify API access and credentials\n108: - Existing integrations module structure\n109: \n110: ### Blocked By\n111: - None\n112: \n113: ### Blocks\n114: - None currently identified\n115: \n116: ### Notes\n117: - Dify integration should be optional and configurable\n118: - Follow existing plugin patterns in the integrations module\n119: - Ensure proper error handling for production use\n120: - Add comprehensive logging for debugging\n\n(End of file - total 120 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-036 — Dify 插件集成 Tasks\n\n**Module**: `integrations`\n**Language**: Python\n**Size**: M\n\n## Task Breakdown\n\n### Task 1: Dify API client implementation\n- [ ] Review Dify API documentation\n- [ ] Design Dify client interface\n- [ ] Implement Dify API client class\n- [ ] Add authentication support\n- [ ] Add error handling\n- [ ] Add request/response logging\n\n**Verification**: Dify client can successfully authenticate and make API calls\n\n---\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-036/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775888812495,"end":1775888812522}}}}
