rkflows are documented\n624: - Documentation is comprehensive\n625: - Troubleshooting guide is provided\n626: - Documentation is accessible from README\n627: \n628: ---\n629: \n630: ### Task 22: Test all workflows end-to-end\n631: - [ ] Trigger ci-pr-checks workflow with test PR\n632: - [ ] Verify all checks pass\n633: - [ ] Trigger lint-checks workflow\n634: - [ ] Verify all linting passes\n635: - [ ] Trigger unit-tests workflow\n636: - [ ] Verify all tests pass and coverage is uploaded\n637: - [ ] Trigger integration-tests workflow\n638: - [ ] Verify all integration tests pass\n639: - [ ] Trigger build-docker workflow\n640: - [ ] Verify Docker images build successfully\n641: - [ ] Trigger security-scan workflow\n642: - [ ] Verify security scans complete\n643: - [ ] Trigger docs-build workflow\n644: - [ ] Verify documentation builds and deploys\n645: - [ ] Test manual trigger workflows\n646: - [ ] Verify notifications are received\n647: - [ ] Document any issues found\n648: \n649: **Verification**:\n650: ```bash\n651: gh run list --workflow=ci-pr-checks.yml\n652: gh run list --workflow=unit-tests.yml\n653: gh run list --workflow=build-docker.yml\n654: ```\n655: \n656: **Acceptance Criteria**:\n657: - All workflows run successfully\n658: - All checks pass\n659: - Notifications are received\n660: - Artifacts are uploaded\n661: - Documentation is deployed\n662: \n663: ---\n664: \n665: ### Task 23: Configure workflow branch protection\n666: - [ ] Configure branch protection for main branch\n667: - [ ] Require ci-pr-checks workflow to pass\n668: - [ ] Require lint-checks workflow to pass\n669: - [ ] Require unit-tests workflow to pass\n670: - [ ] Require status checks to pass before merge\n671: - [ ] Configure required reviewers\n672: - [ ] Configure PR restrictions\n673: - [ ] Configure dismiss stale reviews\n674: - [ ] Configure require signed commits\n675: - [ ] Configure linear history\n676: \n677: **Verification**:\n678: ```bash\n679: gh api repos/:owner/:repo/branches/main/protection\n680: ```\n681: \n682: **Acceptance Criteria**:\n683: - Branch protection is configured\n684: - Required workflows are enforced\n685: - Review requirements are set\n686: - Security settings are enabled\n687: \n688: ---\n689: \n690: ### Task 24: Add workflow security hardening\n691: - [ ] Review all workflows for security best practices\n692: - [ ] Use pinned action versions (not @latest)\n693: - [ ] Use minimal permissions for workflows\n694: - [ ] Configure token permissions (read-only where possible)\n695: - [ ] Add workflow input validation\n696: - [ ] Add secret scanning patterns\n697: - [ ] Configure artifact retention policies\n698: - [ ] Add audit logging\n699: - [ ] Document security considerations\n700: \n701: **Verification**:\n702: ```bash\n703: grep -q \"@v\" .github/workflows/ci-pr-checks.yml && echo \"Pinned versions used\" || echo \"Unpinned versions found\"\n704: grep -q \"permissions:\" .github/workflows/ci-pr-checks.yml && echo \"Permissions configured\" || echo \"Permissions not configured\"\n705: ```\n706: \n707: **Acceptance Criteria**:\n708: - All actions use pinned versions\n709: - Minimal permissions are configured\n710: - Security best practices are followed\n711: - Audit logging is enabled\n712: \n713: ---\n714: \n715: ### Task 25: Create workflow maintenance guide\n716: - [ ] Create workflow maintenance checklist\n717: - [ ] Document workflow update process\n718: - [ ] Document secret rotation process\n719: - [ ] Document workflow troubleshooting steps\n720: - [ ] Document performance tuning guidelines\n721: - [ ] Document backup and recovery procedures\n722: - [ ] Create workflow monitoring dashboard\n723: - [ ] Configure alerts for workflow failures\n724: - [ ] Document escalation procedures\n725: - [ ] Schedule regular workflow reviews\n726: \n727: **Verification**:\n728: ```bash\n729: test -f docs/workflow-maintenance.md && echo \"Maintenance guide exists\" || echo \"Maintenance guide missing\"\n730: grep -q \"troubleshooting\" docs/workflow-maintenance.md && echo \"Troubleshooting documented\" || echo \"Troubleshooting not documented\"\n731: ```\n732: \n733: **Acceptance Criteria**:\n734: - Maintenance guide is comprehensive\n735: - All procedures are documented\n736: - Monitoring is configured\n737: - Escalation procedures are defined\n738: \n739: ---\n740: \n741: ### Task 26: Final validation and cleanup\n742: - [ ] Review all workflows for consistency\n743: - [ ] Ensure all workflows follow naming conventions\n744: - [ ] Verify all workflow comments are accurate\n745: - [ ] Remove any debug or test code\n746: - [ ] Verify all environment variables are documented\n747: - [ ] Verify all secrets are documented\n748: - [ ] Test all workflows one final time\n749: - [ ] Verify documentation is complete\n750: - [ ] Verify badges are working\n751: - [ ] Clean up temporary files\n752: - [ ] Final code review of all workflow files\n753: - [ ] Update CHANGE.md with implementation details\n754: \n755: **Verification**:\n756: ```bash\n757: yamllint .github/workflows/*.yml\n758: find .github -name \"*.tmp\" -o -name \"*.bak\" | wc -l\n759: grep -r \"TODO\\|FIXME\" .github/workflows/\n760: ```\n761: \n762: **Acceptance Criteria**:\n763: - All workflows are consistent and well-documented\n764: - No temporary or debug code remains\n765: - All workflows pass final tests\n766: - Documentation is complete\n767: - CHANGE.md is updated\n768: \n769: ---\n770: \n771: ## Summary\n772: \n773: **Total Tasks**: 26\n774: **Estimated Effort**: L (Large) - 40-60 hours\n775: \n776: ### Key Deliverables\n777: 1. **12 GitHub Actions workflows**:\n778:    - ci-pr-checks.yml - PR validation and checks\n779:    - lint-checks.yml - Code linting across all languages\n780:    - unit-tests.yml - Unit testing with coverage\n781:    - integration-tests.yml - Integration and E2E testing\n782:    - build-docker.yml - Multi-platform Docker builds\n783:    - security-scan.yml - Security vulnerability scanning\n784:    - release.yml - Automated release process\n785:    - deploy-staging.yml - Staging deployment\n786:    - deploy-production.yml - Production deployment\n787:    - docs-build.yml - Documentation build and deployment\n788:    - dependency-update.yml - Automated dependency updates\n789:    - notify-slack.yml - Slack notifications (integrated into workflows)\n790: 2. **5 reusable actions** in .github/actions/\n791: 3. **Configuration files** (Dependabot, CODEOWNERS, templates)\n792: 4. **Documentation** (GitHub Actions guide, maintenance guide)\n793: 5. **Security hardening** and branch protection\n794: 6. **Monitoring and notifications**\n795: \n796: ### Success Criteria\n797: - All 12 workflows are implemented and tested\n798: - Workflows follow GitHub Actions best practices\n799: - All security scans pass (or findings are documented)\n800: - Workflows integrate with existing Makefile build system\n801: - Documentation is comprehensive and accurate\n802: - Branch protection is configured\n803: - Monitoring and notifications are working\n804: - All workflows can be tested locally with act\n805: \n806: ### Dependencies\n807: - AR-033: Makefile build system (workflows depend on Makefile targets)\n808: - AR-032: Dockerfile multi-stage builds (build workflow depends on Dockerfiles)\n809: - GitHub repository with Actions enabled\n810: - Required GitHub secrets (DockerHub, PyPI, Slack, etc.)\n811: - Go 1.21+ toolchain\n812: - Python 3.11+ with pip\n813: - Docker 20.10+\n814: \n815: ### Blocked By\n816: - None (design stage ST-3 completed)\n817: \n818: ### Blocks\n819: - AR-035: Deployment Automation (depends on CI/CD workflows)\n820: - AR-036: Monitoring and Observability (depends on CI/CD workflows)\n821: \n822: ### Notes\n823: - All workflows should use pinned action versions (not @latest)\n824: - Workflows should follow the principle of least privilege\n825: - Caching should be configured for all expensive operations\n826: - All workflows should have appropriate timeouts\n827: - Security scans should block on HIGH/CRITICAL findings\n828: - Production deployments should require manual approval\n829: - Documentation should be kept in sync with workflow changes\n830: - Regular workflow maintenance reviews should be scheduled\n831: - Monitor workflow execution times and optimize as needed\n832: - Use GitHub Environments for deployment workflows\n833: - Consider using GitHub Self-Hosted Runners for private dependencies\n834: - Keep workflow files under version control\n835: - Test workflows locally with act before committing\n836: - Use workflow templates for consistency\n837: - Document any workarounds or temporary solutions\n\n(End of file - total 837 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-034 — CI/CD GitHub Actions (12 workflows) Tasks\n\n**Module**: `.github`\n**Language**: `YAML`\n**Size**: `L`\n**Design Stage**: ST-3 Completed\n\n## Task Breakdown\n\n### Task 1: Create .github directory structure\n- [ ] Create .github/workflows/ directory if it doesn't exist\n- [ ] Create .github/actions/ directory for reusable actions\n- [ ] Create .github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/ directory for issue templates\n- [ ] Create .github/PULL_REQUEST_TEMPLATE/ directory for PR templates\n- [ ] Verify directory permissions are correct\n- [ ] Add .github/ to .gitignore if not already present\n- [ ] Document directory structure in README.md\n\n**Verification**:\n```bash","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-034/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775888821751,"end":1775888821785}}}}
