{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775888922604,"sessionID":"ses_284c75d2fffevadkVQj66gScq2","part":{"id":"prt_d7b3a7773001Bqt5E31N8ECVCM","messageID":"msg_d7b38ee48001PGYXopQkQVDp1A","sessionID":"ses_284c75d2fffevadkVQj66gScq2","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-7ddb435f764f4e98a2114dfa6f7ee745","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-036 — Dify 插件集成 Tasks\n\n**Module**: `integrations`\n**Language**: Python\n**Size**: M\n**Design Stage**: ST-3 Completed\n\n## Task Breakdown\n\n### Task 1: Create integrations module directory structure\n- [ ] Create `integrations/dify-plugin/` directory\n- [ ] Create `integrations/dify-plugin/provider/` directory\n- [ ] Create `integrations/dify-plugin/tools/` directory\n- [ ] Create `integrations/dify-plugin/.difyignore` file\n- [ ] Verify directory permissions are correct\n- [ ] Add `integrations/dify-plugin/` to appropriate .gitignore patterns\n- [ ] Document directory structure in integrations README.md\n\n**Verification**:\n```bash\ntest -d integrations/dify-plugin && echo \"dify-plugin directory exists\" || echo \"dify-plugin directory missing\"\ntest -d integrations/dify-plugin/provider && echo \"provider directory exists\" || echo \"provider directory missing\"\ntest -d integrations/dify-plugin/tools && echo \"tools directory exists\" || echo \"tools directory missing\"\nls -la integrations/dify-plugin/\n```\n\n**Acceptance Criteria**:\n- All required directories are created\n- Directory structure follows Dify plugin conventions\n- Documentation is updated\n\n---\n\n### Task 2: Create plugin manifest.yaml file\n- [ ] Create `integrations/dify-plugin/manifest.yaml`\n- [ ] Set `version: 0.0.2`\n- [ ] Set `type: plugin`\n- [ ] Set `author: volcano-sh`\n- [ ] Set `name: agentcube`\n- [ ] Add multilingual `label` entries (en_US, ja_JP, zh_Hans, pt_BR)\n- [ ] Add multilingual `description` entries\n- [ ] Set `icon: icon.png`\n- [ ] Set `icon_dark: icon-dark.png`\n- [ ] Configure `resource` section with `memory` and `permission` subtree\n- [ ] Add `plugins.tools: [provider/agentcube.yaml]`\n- [ ] Configure `meta` section with `version`, `arch` (amd64, arm64), and `runner`\n- [ ] Set `runner.language: python`, `runner.version: \"3.12\"`, `runner.entrypoint: main`\n- [ ] Set `minimum_dify_version: null`\n- [ ] Add `created_at`, `privacy`, `repo`, `verified` fields\n- [ ] Validate YAML syntax\n\n**Verification**:\n```bash\ntest -f integrations/dify-plugin/manifest.yaml && echo \"manifest.yaml exists\" || echo \"manifest.yaml missing\"\nyamllint integrations/dify-plugin/manifest.yaml || echo \"YAML syntax valid\"\ngrep -q \"type: plugin\" integrations/dify-plugin/manifest.yaml && echo \"Plugin type configured\" || echo \"Plugin type missing\"\ngrep -q \"plugins.tools\" integrations/dify-plugin/manifest.yaml && echo \"Tools configured\" || echo \"Tools missing\"\n```\n\n**Acceptance Criteria**:\n- manifest.yaml follows exact Dify plugin structure\n- All required fields are present and correctly formatted\n- YAML syntax is valid\n- Multilingual labels are properly configured\n\n---\n\n### Task 3: Create provider descriptor YAML file\n- [ ] Create `integrations/dify-plugin/provider/agentcube.yaml`\n- [ ] Configure `identity.author: agentcube`\n- [ ] Configure `identity.name: agentcube`\n- [ ] Add multilingual `identity.label` entries\n- [ ] Add multilingual `identity.description` entries\n- [ ] Set `identity.icon`\n- [ ] Add commented `oauth_schema` block (not active)\n- [ ] Configure `tools: [tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml]`\n- [ ] Set `extra.python.source: provider/agentcube.py`\n- [ ] Validate YAML syntax\n\n**Verification**:\n```bash\ntest -f integrations/dify-plugin/provider/agentcube.yaml && echo \"agentcube.yaml exists\" || echo \"agentcube.yaml missing\"\nyamllint integrations/dify-plugin/provider/agentcube.yaml || echo \"YAML syntax valid\"\ngrep -q \"identity:\" integrations/dify-plugin/provider/agentcube.yaml && echo \"Identity configured\" || echo \"Identity missing\"\ngrep -q \"extra.python.source\" integrations/dify-plugin/provider/agentcube.yaml && echo \"Python source configured\" || echo \"Python source missing\"\n```\n\n**Acceptance Criteria**:\n- Provider descriptor follows correct structure\n- Identity information is complete\n- Tools are properly referenced\n- Python source is correctly configured\n\n---\n\n### Task 4: Create tool descriptor YAML file\n- [ ] Create `integrations/dify-plugin/tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml`\n- [ ] Configure `identity.name: agentcube-code-interpreter`\n- [ ] Configure `identity.author: agentcube`\n- [ ] Add multilingual `identity.label` entries\n- [ ] Add multilingual `identity.description` entries\n- [ ] Add `router_url` parameter (string, required, form type)\n- [ ] Add `workload_manager_url` parameter (string, required, form type)\n- [ ] Add `language` parameter (select, optional, llm type, options: python, javascript, typescript)\n- [ ] Add `code` parameter (string, optional, llm type)\n- [ ] Add `command` parameter (string, optional, llm type)\n- [ ] Add `session_id` parameter (string, optional, llm type)\n- [ ] Add `session_reuse` parameter (boolean, optional, llm type)\n- [ ] Add `code_interpreter_id` parameter (string, optional, llm type)\n- [ ] Configure proper `label`, `human_description`, `llm_description` for each parameter\n- [ ] Set `extra.python.source: tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.py`\n- [ ] Validate YAML syntax\n\n**Verification**:\n```bash\ntest -f integrations/dify-plugin/tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml && echo \"tool descriptor exists\" || echo \"tool descriptor missing\"\nyamllint integrations/dify-plugin/tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml || echo \"YAML syntax valid\"\ngrep -q \"router_url\" integrations/dify-plugin/tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml && echo \"router_url configured\" || echo \"router_url missing\"\ngrep -q \"language\" integrations/dify-plugin/tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml && echo \"language configured\" ||